\b 4. RESULTS AND DISCUSSION (PPT READY)\b0\par
\par
This version is simplified for presentation slides. It keeps only the most important findings, avoids heavy theory, and focuses on visible results, key numbers, and clear conclusions.\par
\par
\b What To Include In The PPT\b0\par
1. Qualitative comparison of Model 1, Model 2, and Model 3 on EUVP samples.\par
2. Quantitative comparison table using UCIQE, UIQM, PSNR, and SSIM.\par
3. One failure case and one over-enhancement case for Model 3.\par
4. Cross-domain examples from UIEB and RUIE.\par
5. Short ablation study showing the effect of edge loss and color loss.\par
6. Final takeaway slide: Model 2 is best balanced, Model 3 is best visually.\par
\par
\b 4.1 Visual Enhancement For Quality Comparison\b0\par
\par
\b Slide Title Suggestion:\b0 Qualitative Comparison of the Three Models\par
\par
\b Figure suggestions:\b0\par
- Model 1 triplet grid: results/euvp_triplet_grids/model1_euvp_triplet_grid.png\par
- Model 2 triplet grid: results/euvp_triplet_grids/model2_euvp_triplet_grid.png\par
- Model 3 triplet grid: results/euvp_triplet_grids/model3_euvp_triplet_grid.png\par
- 4-panel random comparison: results/samples/random_model_comparison_grid_v2.png\par
\par
\b Short slide bullets:\b0\par
- Model 1 improves brightness and visibility, but enhancement is conservative.\par
- Model 2 gives stronger contrast and better color correction than Model 1.\par
- Model 3 gives the strongest visual enhancement and the clearest subject-background separation.\par
- Overall visual quality improves progressively from Model 1 to Model 3.\par
\par
\b Model 1 key point:\b0 Good baseline enhancement, but weaker color correction and detail recovery.\par
\b Model 2 key point:\b0 Better contrast and better balance between enhancement and structure preservation.\par
\b Model 3 key point:\b0 Best visual restoration across low-light, green-cast, and low-contrast examples.\par
\par
\b Optional presenter line:\b0 "Qualitatively, the results show a clear progression: Model 1 provides basic improvement, Model 2 strengthens contrast and color recovery, and Model 3 produces the strongest and most consistent enhancement."\par
\par
